See important comments concerning validity of position given in sectionNavigation Output Filters.This message outputs the Geodetic position with high precision in the currently selectedellipsoid. The default is the WGS84 Ellipsoid, but can be changed with the messageCFG-DAT.

column7: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch.See the description of iTOW for details.
High precision component of longitude. Mustbe in the range -99..+99. Precise longitude indeg * 1e-7 = lon + (lonHp * 1e-2).
High precision component of latitude. Must bein the range -99..+99. Precise latitude in deg *1e-7 = lat + (latHp * 1e-2).
